<br>
<br>
<br>
That's the rub right there. I dont really care at all what it looks like, although I think the landscape is absolutely stunning, it's all about the immersion and the playstyle. <br>
<br>
I have never ever felt more comfortable roleplaying a character, or making friends and social aquaintences, than I have in Horizons. It's all about community and working together, and really making a story out of it instead of just &quot;Work on goal x, finish, proceed to goal y, finish, etc..&quot;<br>
<br>
I agree that the characters are a bit boarish, however. I really dont like how my Fiend looks anymore. I'm in love with the blue skin, horns, and tail of course.. but I wanted more detail. Basically I wanted the SW:G character creation for this game, and I think they could have done that. But with the character loading issues that have been mentioned....I could see how that would be a nightmare. Just give it time, is my best suggestion. *shrug* All these games had to start somewhere.. and EQ is still in beta. o.O<br>
<br>
